JOHANNESBURG - Police in the Eastern Cape have arrested two suspects on stock theft charges after finding six sheep crammed inside a Toyota Tazz. In a Tweet on Sunday, the South African Police Service confirmed the incident, which took place in Cathcart - a small town between Stutterheim and Queenstown. #sapsEC Carthcat #SAPS members arrested two suspects for #StockTheft last night. Six sheep were recovered in the vehicle. Both suspects will appear before Cartchart Magistrate Court soon. NP pic.twitter.com/xrXKuUmsCB READ: ANC condemns stock theft case involving MP released on a warning The suspects will appear in court on Monday.  (Photo: Saps) eNCA